@jihoonson 
Thank you for listing. But, if we add all guys who open Jira issues, we will add all guys who report bugs.  I think that It's not meaningful to both me and them. It has to be worth to put the name on contributor list. In addition, Min already is a committer. Jinhang seems to continue contribution.So, I agree with him. But, other guys worked long time ago. We can add them if they start contribution again or their code is committed. 

If we need more discussion or need some rule for it, we should create another jira issue. This issue is for adding Alvin to committer list.

I did the follows:
- I've rebased the patch against the latest source code.
- I've fixed unit test failures by adding some workaround code as follows:

```
  @AfterClass
  public static void tearDown() {
    testingCluster.setAllTajoDaemonConfValue(
        ConfVars.EXECUTOR_INNER_JOIN_INMEMORY_HASH_THRESHOLD.varname,
        String.valueOf(ConfVars.EXECUTOR_INNER_JOIN_INMEMORY_HASH_THRESHOLD.defaultLongVal));
    testingCluster.setAllTajoDaemonConfValue(ConfVars.EXECUTOR_OUTER_JOIN_INMEMORY_HASH_THRESHOLD.varname,
        String.valueOf(ConfVars.EXECUTOR_OUTER_JOIN_INMEMORY_HASH_THRESHOLD.defaultLongVal));
    testingCluster.setAllTajoDaemonConfValue(ConfVars.EXECUTOR_GROUPBY_INMEMORY_HASH_THRESHOLD.varname,
        String.valueOf(ConfVars.EXECUTOR_GROUPBY_INMEMORY_HASH_THRESHOLD.defaultLongVal));
  }
```

After than, the patch works well. the patch nice to me.  Here is my +1. I'll commit it soon.

Thanks!
